New Records: Gunnar Henderson hit a two-run home run in the second inning, extending the Orioles' streak of at least two decisions without being swept.
Grayson Rodriguez pitched eight outstanding innings, striking out seven without a walk.
Key Match Events: Gunnar Henderson set the tone early with a first-pitch single and later hit a two-run home run in the second inning.
Grayson Rodriguez allowed five hits in a career-high eight innings.
Post-Match Reflections: Baltimore Orioles’ manager Brandon Hyde praised Gunnar Henderson’s performance.
The Orioles secured a potentially crucial tiebreaker in the AL East with an 8-0 victory.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Tampa Bay Rays put INF Taylor Walls on the paternity list and selected the contract of INF Tristan Gray from Triple-A Durham.
The Orioles recalled RHP Mike Baumann from Triple-A Norfolk and optioned RHP Bryan Baker to Norfolk.
